thread.title_full: Georgia lottery: N. Fulton Kroger sells $50K Powerball ticket

author: Becca J. G. Godwin
title: Georgia lottery: N. Fulton Kroger sells $50K Powerball ticket
text:
A lottery player in north Fulton County did not win the $310 million Powerball jackpot Wednesday — but they did win a decent chunk of change.
The winning numbers drawn were 5-28-33-38-42 and the Powerball was 19.
A Kroger, located at 3000 Old Alabama Road in Alpharetta, sold a $50,000 ticket matching the first four numbers. A Publix in Savannah did the same.
MORE: Did that N. Fulton teacher win the $20K Grammy Foundation award?
MORE: Which N. Fulton high schools ranked as some of the best in Georgia?
A lottery player in Cherokee County got even closer; a convenience store on the Cobb line sold a $1 million ticket . The Georgia Lottery was not immediately available to confirm if the tickets had been claimed.
Saturday’s Powerball jackpot is an estimated $349 million.
